      "comment_id" : 39114901,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "These are not byte literals. They are literals of a variety of other types (int, mostly) that are being implicitly converted to a byte.  e.g., <code>1</code> is an int literal, but <code>double d = 1;</code> compiles just fine."
